Sentencas: Solid oxide cells (SOCs) are highly efficient energy conversion systems, offering switchable capabilities for power and fuel production.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells

Sentencas: NiFe metal-supported structures in SOCs show promising advantages in structural stability and scalability.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells

Sentencas: This study explores the synergistic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion in NiFe-supported SOCs, enhancing alloy catalyst formation in the electrode and improving the sinterability of the zirconia-based electrolyte.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells

Sentencas: This results in increased activity for carbon fuel reactions, resistance to coking, and a remarkably low ohmic resistance of 0.06 Omega cm 2 at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The NiFe support also enhances structural stability, enabling reversible and multifuel operation.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The single cell achieves exceptional maximum power densities of 2.6 and 2.0 W cm -2 in fuel cell mode (3 % H 2 O/H 2 and dry CO) and current densities of - 1.51 and - 1.38 A cm -2 in electrolysis cell mode (1.3 V, 20 % H 2 O/H 2 and 20 % CO 2 /CO) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Synergetic effect of spontaneous Fe diffusion for enabling immediately switchable operations in NiFe-supported solid oxide cells
